<title>USA: Pa. transit agency unveils $717 mln budget plan.</title>
<headline>Pa. transit agency unveils $717 mln budget plan.</headline>
<dateline>PHILADELPHIA 1997-05-08</dateline>
<text>
<p>Southeastern Pennsylvania Transportation Authority has unveiled a $717 million budget proposal that includes no fare hikes or service cuts.</p>
<p>Although SEPTA said it would use attrition to cut its workforce by about seven percent, the agency is not ruling out layoffs.</p>
<p>Officials at the mass transit agency said layoffs would be more likely if they are unable to control growing workman's compensation costs.</p>
<p>The agency's board is expected to vote on the spending proposal at its June meeting.</p>
<p>--U.S. Municipal Desk, 212-859-1650</p>
